origin":2684,"position":0},"title":"Ibn Mubarak on Akhlaq: Good character is to abandon anger","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 22, 2018","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Rajab reported: It was said to Ibn al-Mubarak, may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cSummarize good character for us in a single sentence.\u201d Ibn al-Mubarak said, \u201cLeave aside anger.\u201d Ibn Rajab said, \u201cThe same explanation was offered by Imam Ahmad and Ishaq ibn Rahawayh, that good character is to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24253,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/01\/09\/baqir-character-kindness-all-good\/","url_meta":{"origin":2684,"position":1},"title":"Baqir on Character: Kindness and good character all that is good","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 9, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Mubarak reported: Muhammad ibn Ali al-Baqir, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cWhoever has qualities of character and kindness has been given all that is good and comforting. His situation will be pleasant in his life and in his Hereafter. Whoever is deprived of qualities of kindness and\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17565,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/01\/11\/enrich-akhlaq-smiling\/","url_meta":{"origin":2684,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Akhlaq: Enrich people with good character, smiling","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 11, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, you cannot enrich all of the people with your wealth, but rather you enrich them with your cheerful faces and good character.\u201d Source: Shu\u2019ab al-Ima\u0304n lil-Bayhaqi\u0304 7695 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Suyuti \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":27768,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/04\/17\/ibn-mubarak-adab-first-salaf\/","url_meta":{"origin":2684,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Mubarak on Adab: Seek manners before other Islamic sciences","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 17, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn al-Jazari reported: Ibn al-Mubarak, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cI sought manners for thirty years and I sought sacred knowledge for twenty years. The righteous predecessors would seek manners first, then seek knowledge.\u201d Source:\u00a0Gha\u0304yat al-Niha\u0304yah 1\/446 \u0639\u0646 \u0627\u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u062c\u0632\u0631\u064a \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u0628\u062f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0628\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0645\u0628\u0627\u0631\u0643 \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0637\u0644\u0628\u062a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22202,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/03\/12\/need-manners-more-knowledge\/","url_meta":{"origin":2684,"position":4},"title":"Ibn Mubarak on Character: You need manners more than knowledge","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"March 12, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn 'Asakir reported: Ibn al-Mubarak, may Allah have mercy on him, said to the people of hadith, \"You are in greater need of a little manners than a great deal of knowledge.\u201d Source: Ta\u0304ri\u0304kh Dimashq 32918 Ibn al-Qayyim said, \u201cThe reality of manners is that it results from beautiful character.\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37396,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/18\/bad-character-spoils-deeds\/","url_meta":{"origin":2684,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Akhlaq: Bad character spoils good deeds","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 18, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, bad character spoils deeds just as vinegar spoils honey.\u201d Source: Musnad 'Abd ibn H\u0323umayd 799 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u0651\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0646\u0651\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0625\u0650\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0633\u064f\u0648\u0621\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064f\u0644\u064f\u0642\u0650 \u0644\u064e\u064a\u064f\u0641\u0652\u0633\u065